# Curated core security-research set. Heavy/GUI tools (metasploit, burp,
# ghidra) intentionally left for on-demand install.
nmap
wireshark
tcpdump
binwalk
john
hashcat
sqlmap
aircrack-ng
hydra
gobuster
netcat-openbsd
whois
bind9-dnsutils
# radare2 is not in Debian trixie — it's installed from the Kali repo
# (extras/kali/kali-tools.list) on the security edition, or on demand via
# `apt install radare2` on any edition that ships the Kali repo.
